Server Info the Reference Implementation to test out scenarios:

GROUP DISCOVERY
::::::::::::::::

  1. Group discovery with name parameter
    Get:https://52.70.192.201/bulk-api-r4/fhir/Group?name=Test Group 5
    Header: Content-Type: application/fhir+json

  2. Group discovery with identifier System|type|value
    Get: https://52.70.192.201/bulk-api-r4/fhir/Group?identifier=http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v2-0203|NPI|7316876424&identifier=http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v2-0203|TAX|963258741
    Header: Content-Type: application/fhir+json

GROUP EXPORT
::::::::::::::

  1. Group export by id. Export a detailed set of FHIR resources of diverse resource types pertaining to all patients in specified Group
    Get: https://52.70.192.201/bulk-api-r4/fhir/Group/2/$export
    Header:
    Accept: application/fhir+json
    Prefer: respond-async

  2. Content-Location header with the absolute URL of an endpoint for subsequent status requests (polling location). A body containing a JSON object providing metadata, and links to the generated bulk data files. The files SHALL be accessible to the client at the URLs advertised. These URLs MAY be served by file servers other than a FHIR-specific server.
    Get: https://52.70.192.201/bulk-api-r4/bulkdata/44

  3. File Request.Using the URLs supplied by the FHIR server in the Complete Status response body, a client MAY download the generated bulk data files
    Get: https://52.70.192.201/bulk-api-r4/bulkdata/download/44/Patient.ndjson
I want to thank you for all the participants.
